{"questionId":"3216546","questionHtml":"<p>Hence find the area of the triangular cover.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><strong>METHOD 1</strong></p>\n<p>attempt to use the vector product formula for the area of triangle</p>\n<p>(condone incorrect signs and missing <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math>) &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>area <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><msqrt><msup><mn>3</mn><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><msup><mn>7</mn><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><msup><mn>42</mn><mn>2</mn></msup></msqrt></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>21</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>3</mn><mo> </mo><mo>(</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>)</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>(</mo><mn>21</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>3424</mn><mo>…</mo><mo>,</mo><mo> </mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><msqrt><mn>1822</mn></msqrt><mo>)</mo></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>METHOD 2</strong></p>\n<p>find <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>θ</mi></math> using <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mover><mi>AB</mi><mo>→</mo></mover><mo>×</mo><mover><mi>AC</mi><mo>→</mo></mover><mo>=</mo><mfenced open=\"|\" close=\"|\"><mover><mi>AB</mi><mo>→</mo></mover></mfenced><mfenced open=\"|\" close=\"|\"><mover><mi>AC</mi><mo>→</mo></mover></mfenced><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mi>θ</mi></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>θ</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>67</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>1</mn></math> (<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>67</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>1350</mn><mo>°</mo><mo>…</mo><mo>,</mo><mo> </mo><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>171728</mn><mo>…</mo></math> radians)</p>\n<p>then area <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mfenced open=\"|\" close=\"|\"><mover><mi>AB</mi><mo>→</mo></mover></mfenced><mfenced open=\"|\" close=\"|\"><mover><mi>AC</mi><mo>→</mo></mover></mfenced><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mi>θ</mi></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>21</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>3</mn><mo> </mo><mo>(</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>)</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>21</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>3424</mn><mo>…</mo><mo>,</mo><mo> </mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><msqrt><mn>1822</mn></msqrt></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>","meta":{"questionId":"3216546","referenceCode":"23M.1.AHL.TZ1.7b","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Hence find the area of the triangular cover.","paper":"1","level":"HL","questionNumber":"b","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 3—Geometry and trigonometry","Topic 3—Geometry and trigonometry","AHL 3.13—Scalar and vector products"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}